**CSS Reading Summary**
 *CSS*
 > Cascading Style Sheet (CSS)
 - CSS allows you to create rules that specify how content of element should appear
 - With CSS imagine that there is an invisible box around every HTML element.
 - CSS allows you to create rules that controlthe way each box is presented.
 - CSS properties affect how elements are displayed.

 **CSS Color**
 > Color brings web pages to life!
 - Foreground color: allows you to specify color of text insidean element.
 - Background color: is chosen using RGB values, hex codes, and color names.
 - Contrast: when picking a fore ground and background colors pay attentionto the contrast, and make sure there is enough of a contrast for the text to be legible.
 - CSS introduces a new way to specify colors using hue, saturation, and light value.

